      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that government control stifles innovation is a consistently used talking point by those who prefer private, market-driven systems. While some localized inefficiencies exist in any large system, the core claim that government involvement inherently halts medical breakthroughs is a massive oversimplification. Real-world evidence shows that centralized systems can direct massive resources toward public health crises and research that the private sector ignores. The focus should be on *how* the system is managed, not on the inherent danger of collective provision.",
